visualizations.description:
Objective: To monitor registration efforts

Calculation:
- Num: # registered households / population
- Den: # estimated households / population

Action:
If significantly under 100%:
- Check if nearby areas are over 100% (e.g. population movement).
- Consider how birth and death rates might have affected estimates.
- Consider the source and quality of the estimated data (e.g. how long ago was the census, was modelled data used).
- Follow up with areas in case agents need support (possible incomplete reporting or missed households)

Objective: To account for all campaign ITNs and highlight variances

Calculation: # ITNs remaining (theoretical) minus # ITNs remaining (reported)

Action: If not 0, investigate where the variances occurred and correct data in system accordingly. Continue this until national variance is 0.
